Extract reverse geocoding results

Source: R/utils.R
extract_reverse_results.Rd

Parses the output of the query_api function for reverse geoocding. The address is extracted into the first column of the returned dataframe. This function is not used for batch geocoded results. Refer to query_api for example usage.

extract_reverse_results(method, response, full_results = TRUE, flatten = TRUE)

Arguments

method

method name
response

content from the geocoder service (returned by the query_api function)
full_results

if TRUE then the full results (not just an address column) will be returned.
flatten

if TRUE then flatten any nested dataframe content

Value

geocoder results in tibble format

See also

get_api_query query_api reverse_geo
